    "created_at": "2023-12-01T11:42:27Z",
    "updated_at": "2023-12-01T11:42:27Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The problem with `--exitwhensynced` is that there are two ways for us to sync post-merge. \r\nThe first way, where `--exitwhensynced` still works is if the beacon node provides us a head and we start snap syncing (or full syncing) to that head. \r\nThe other way is if the beacon node provides us blocks one by one. In this scenario we don't know when we arrived at the head and finished our sync. \r\n\r\nIn most cases the beacon node will use the first way, only if you shut down a synced beacon node and restarted will it use the second way. What you can do is to specify a pretty recent synctarget via `--synctarget` which will instruct your node to try to sync to this target and stop or you use the script that @AusIV provided.\r\n\r\nI'm closing this for now since there is not much that we can do about it, since only the beacon node knows whether we are truly synced or not post-merge.",
